# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build / runtime artefacts
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.log

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Data, weights, results (large, regenerable, never committed)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
checkpoints/
result/
result_*/

# Model weight blobs are big and regenerable; ignore by default.
# The stereo-depth weights are an exception: they're a stable, vendored
# third-party asset (89 MB) that doesn't change across denoiser iterations,
# so it lives in the repo to make `git clone` + `python benchmark/run.py`
# work out of the box. The denoiser ONNX is the *artefact under test* and
# updates every training run — ship those out-of-band, don't track.
*.pth
*.onnx
!benchmark/depth/weights.pth

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# benchmark/ pipeline outputs (regenerable; big — ~400 MB of PNGs per run)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
benchmark/output/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local-only archive of every artefact / intermediate the project produced
# during the four experiment phases (16-strategy sweep, 7-hour 92-candidate
# research, 3-hour robust push, 6-candidate perceptual sweep). The text-form
# distillation lives in docs/EXPERIMENTS_JOURNEY.md and is tracked; this
# folder contains the raw artefacts (HTML reports, ckpts, asset PNGs,
# tar.gz / zip bundles, intermediate loss-curve images, deprecated scripts)
# kept locally for reference but never pushed.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
_archive_local/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auxiliary ckpt directory used by ad-hoc / experimental training scripts.
# The directory is regenerable, so it stays out of git.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
ckpts/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Distribution archives produced by `git archive ...` for handing off the
# repo to other machines.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.zip
*.tar.gz

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Loss / progress images that get regenerated by training pipelines.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
loss_curves*.png
*_curves.png

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor / OS noise
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
